    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today's slate with a lineup heavily incentivized by favorable matchups against sub-par arms, led by the elite start of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98). Despite the uncertainty regarding his final batting order, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our highest-rated asset today, projected to feast on the 5.52 xERA of Sasaki; his high-upside speed profile aligns perfectly with our organizational mandate to capture every possible stolen base. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Trea Turner** (70.16) provide excellent efficiency against vulnerable pitching. **Trea Turner** remains our premier engine for the week, benefiting from a soft matchup against Elder, while **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62) carries a similarly strong profile, backed by an elite xwOBA that necessitates a high-leverage start.\n\nWe have strategically optimized for platoon edges and park factors to bolster our bottom-line production. **Caleb Durbin** (55.61) is a prime example of park-adjusted value, seeing a massive +16% boost due to favorable hitting conditions that outweigh his bottom-of-the-order placement. Meanwhile, **Colt Keith** (61.81) continues to be an everyday anchor, leveraging a +7% platoon advantage to remain firmly in our 60+ \"Strong\" start tier. We were forced to bench **Victor Scott II** (38.48), who hovered dangerously close to our selection threshold but ultimately fell short due to a brutal -17% SP skill penalty against Woo and a suppressed -8% impact from the nine-hole. While **Victor Scott II** offers the speed we covet, his lack of offensive output against high-tier pitching makes him a risky start compared to the efficiency provided by **Chase Meidroth** (50.85).\n\nManagers should remain alert to the status of **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, whose \"Lineup Pending\" tag introduces non-zero variance to his high projection. While we have accounted for **Carson Benge** being sidelined by a rainout and the ongoing injury recovery of **Christian Yelich**, the depth of the roster\u2014including potential reinforcements like **Zac Veen**, **Luke Raley**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Josh Smith**, and **Luis Pena**\u2014allows us to preserve our game caps while keeping our floor high. With **Gary Sanchez** confirmed on the bench, our focus remains strictly on maximizing volume from our top 11, ensuring we capitalize on today\u2019s prime opportunities to climb the 5x5 Roto standings.",
